{
  "hook": "Your 3D prints keep failing? Check these 6 mistakes.",
  "headline": "6 Common 3D Printing Mistakes and How to Fix Them",
  "body": [
    "Most print failures come from the same handful of mistakes",
    "Fix these six and watch your success rate soar",
    "Simple adjustments, massive improvement"
  ],
  "insight": "The majority of 3D print failures stem from just a few common mistakes: poor bed leveling, wrong temperatures, thin walls, no supports, wet filament, and excessive speed.",
  "source": "All3DP, Sovol3D, Prusa Research",
  "source_url": "https://all3dp.com/1/common-3d-printing-problems-troubleshooting-3d-printer-issues/",
  "pillar": "education",
  "account": "cu-circuits",
  "hashtags": ["#3DPrinting", "#3DPrintingTips", "#FDM", "#AdditiveManufacturing", "#MakerCommunity", "#CuCircuits", "#Prototyping", "#HardwareTips"],
  "caption": "Your 3D prints keep failing and you cannot figure out why?\n\nIt is almost always one of these six mistakes.\n\nWe run 3D printers daily at Cu Circuits for prototyping enclosures and jigs. After thousands of prints, we have seen every failure mode. And the fix is usually simpler than you think.\n\n1. Skipping bed leveling (the #1 cause of first layer failures)\n2. Wrong temperature for your material\n3. Walls too thin to actually print solid\n4. Printing overhangs without supports\n5. Using filament that absorbed moisture\n6. Printing too fast for your setup\n\nSave this card. Next time a print fails, check these six things first before you blame the printer.\n\nWhat is your most common print failure? Share below.\n\n#3DPrinting #3DPrintingTips #FDM #AdditiveManufacturing #MakerCommunity #CuCircuits #Prototyping #HardwareTips",
  "strategy": {"format": "tip_cards_grid", "visual_approach": "2x3 grid of tip cards with numbers, bold titles, and one line fixes"},
  "html": "<div style=\"width:1080px; height:1350px; background:#0a0a0a; position:relative; overflow:hidden; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;\">\n\n  <!-- Top accent line -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:3px; background:#ff6600;\"></div>\n\n  <!-- Cu Logo -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:40px; left:48px; width:36px; height:36px; background:#006644; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;\">\n    <span style=\"font-size:16px; font-weight:800; color:#fff; letter-spacing:0.5px;\">Cu</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Label -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:44px; left:100px;\">\n    <span style=\"font-size:16px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4); letter-spacing:4px; text-transform:uppercase;\">Quick Fix Guide</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Header -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:110px; left:48px; right:48px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:160px; font-weight:900; color:#ff6600; line-height:0.85; letter-spacing:-8px;\">6</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:48px; font-weight:900; color:#fff; margin-top:8px; letter-spacing:-2px; line-height:1.1;\">Common 3D Printing<br>Mistakes</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:18px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4); margin-top:12px;\">And the one line fix for each</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- 2x3 Grid -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:430px; left:48px; right:48px; display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:16px;\">\n\n    <!-- Card 1 -->\n    <div style=\"width:476px; background:rgba(255,102,0,0.06); border:1px solid rgba(255,102,0,0.15); padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:14px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:42px; font-weight:900; color:rgba(255,102,0,0.3); line-height:1;\">01</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:700; color:#fff;\">Skipping Bed Leveling</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:15px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55); line-height:1.5;\">Level before every print. Paper test at all four corners. Nozzle should barely grip.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 2 -->\n    <div style=\"width:476px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:14px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:42px; font-weight:900; color:rgba(255,102,0,0.3); line-height:1;\">02</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:700; color:#fff;\">Wrong Nozzle Temperature</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:15px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55); line-height:1.5;\">PLA 190 to 220. ABS 230 to 250. PETG 220 to 250. Always match your filament brand.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 3 -->\n    <div style=\"width:476px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:14px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:42px; font-weight:900; color:rgba(255,102,0,0.3); line-height:1;\">03</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:700; color:#fff;\">Walls Too Thin</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:15px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55); line-height:1.5;\">Minimum wall: 2 to 3x nozzle diameter. For 0.4mm nozzle, walls should be 0.8mm or more.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 4 -->\n    <div style=\"width:476px; background:rgba(255,102,0,0.06); border:1px solid rgba(255,102,0,0.15); padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:14px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:42px; font-weight:900; color:rgba(255,102,0,0.3); line-height:1;\">04</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:700; color:#fff;\">No Support Structures</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:15px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55); line-height:1.5;\">Overhangs beyond 45 degrees need supports. Use tree supports for cleaner removal.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 5 -->\n    <div style=\"width:476px; background:rgba(255,102,0,0.06); border:1px solid rgba(255,102,0,0.15); padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:14px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:42px; font-weight:900; color:rgba(255,102,0,0.3); line-height:1;\">05</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:700; color:#fff;\">Wet Filament</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:15px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55); line-height:1.5;\">Moisture causes bubbling and weak layers. Store in sealed bags with desiccant. Dry before use.</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 6 -->\n    <div style=\"width:476px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:14px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:42px; font-weight:900; color:rgba(255,102,0,0.3); line-height:1;\">06</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:700; color:#fff;\">Printing Too Fast</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:15px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55); line-height:1.5;\">Start at 40 to 60mm/s for detailed parts. Speed kills quality. Nail the basics first.</div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Bottom insight -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; bottom:80px; left:48px; right:48px; border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); padding-top:16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:18px; font-weight:300; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45); line-height:1.5;\">Fix these six first. Most print failures come from this same short list, not from the printer itself.</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Footer -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; bottom:28px; left:48px; right:48px; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);\">cucircuits.com</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);\">Source: All3DP, Sovol3D, Prusa Research</div>\n  </div>\n\n</div>"
}
